[DAY 30] ENTITY STATE TRANSITIONS:
  new Entity()         → TRANSIENT (not tracked, not in DB)
  persist(entity)       → MANAGED   (tracked, INSERT on flush)
  TX ends              → DETACHED  (has data, not tracked)
  detach(entity)        → DETACHED  (explicit)
  merge(detached)       → MANAGED   (new managed copy returned)
  save(detached)        → MANAGED   (Spring JPA calls merge internally)
  remove(managed)       → REMOVED   (DELETE on flush)

  PRODUCTION RULES:
  1. NEVER modify a detached entity and expect auto-save.
  2. Call save() after modifying detached entities.
  3. Prefer loading entities fresh within the TX boundary.
  4. Use DTOs to avoid passing managed/detached entities across layers.

